CRON_SERVICE_MINIMUM_DURATION_BETWEEN_SYNC_DATA_IN_MILLISECONDS - Static variable in class eu.focusnet.app.util.Constant.AppConfig
We do not allow data synchronization to occur too often and this constant defines the minimum interval between 2 consecutive data synchronizations.
CRON_SERVICE_POLLING_INTERVAL_IN_MINUTES - Static variable in class eu.focusnet.app.util.Constant.AppConfig
Periodic tasks are run only once every Constant.AppConfig.CRON_SERVICE_REFRESH_DATA_PERIOD_IN_MINUTES, but this value is quite high and the user may not be using the application for that long before putting his device in sleep mode.

CronService - Class in eu.focusnet.app.controller
This class is a service responsible for calling periodic tasks: - retrieving new version of data every N minutes

Schedulor behavior regarding sleep/wake: - will not wake the device up - we use wake locks to ensure that started tasks are indeed finished - when waking up, the device will wait for Constant.AppConfig#CRON_SERVICE_POLLING_INTERVAL_IN_MINUTES before trying to execute the tasks again - When an execution is triggered, we then make sure we do not execute the sync/clean tasks too often by comparing the last execution time with Constant.AppConfig#CRON_SERVICE_REFRESH_DATA_PERIOD_IN_MINUTES.
